  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class ModifyingUserFailedException
extends SimulatorException
    This exception is thrown when modifying user data fails. This could be, for example, caused by the user being non existent and therefore unable to be modified or a failed writing operation on the file system.
    Since:
    1.5
    Author:
    dpottkaemper
